sc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/umephergreatfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mepher Greatfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Torvonnite</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#122950>(2/1/02 4:25:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2445.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire, FCFS or Rotation?</span><hr size=1> HAHAHAH You have to be kidding me!!  You honestly believe that Rage will sit up a while if he is fcfs?  The whole point of making him fcfs is so he doesnt sit while guild A takes 2 days trying to get their shit together.<br><br>If all the guilds with an ounce of initiave dont need Rage and he sits there untouched then you can get off your ass and finally do something rather than talk all day.  How about if we all stop debating so much and just go kill.<br><br>Im sick of hearing how we &quot;NEED&quot; this rotation to make it fair.  Make it fair for who?  GuildA that is always ready gets to watch Rage sit there while GuildB spends 2 days trying to get their shit together.  How is that fair?<br><br>Im normally quite reserved when I post on this board but enough is enough.  Rage should be fcfs like all the other epic mobs out there with the exception of the notoriously flawed VS rotation.  Look at that as an example of how bad this will be.<br><br>I've seen about 20 new threads in the last month debating Ragefire.  Verant took a step to ease the problem and you want to put us back in the exact same boat.  Jhonno....hate to single you out here but you must spend more time on this board than you do in game.   Maybe a few less posts and you might actually have your epic by now.<br><br>Mepher<br>Eternal Rage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C5C5BA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uatylla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atylla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Torvonnite</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#122950>(2/1/02 5:12:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2445.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire, FCFS or Rotation?</span><hr size=1> FCFS.  <br><br>If Rage is spawning in Skyfire, then even a younger epic capable guild, can do some xp raiding in the zone, while waiting for Rage to rear it's head.  By going FCFS, you substitute raw desire AND/or ability for cumbersome and inefficient "lists".<br><br>In this instance, a younger guild, raiding IN ZONE, has a better chance of getting their Epic SOONER than if on a list.  How?  Simple.<br><br>You claim that lists are what allows smaller guilds to get their epics at all.  In fact, the adherence to the list, artificially retards your ability to get your epic upon being Rage ready.  So really, by having a list, you make each and every cleric wait MONTHS for their epic.<br><br>Your ultimate fear, is that a guild such as Sacro, BoW, IR, or NoF will by sheer ability screw you out of your chance to get your epic.  Fear based on their ability to mobilize quickly, and dispose of what is to them an easy spawn.  But these guilds typically don't have that URGENT need to mobilize the instant Rage is up.  They have epic wielding clerics of their own.  You think they will up and leave a NToV raid just to gank Rage from a young guild?  Not that likely.  Possible, but not likely.<br><br>Instead, you collectively, and submissively, screw yourselves over by deferring to a vast list once you are ready for Rage.<br><br>In any event, a guild such as HA, with NO epic clerics (AFAIK), and easily capable of dropping Rage quickly would HUGELY benefit from this scenario.  HA needs an epic cleric VERY badly.  I suspect that if Rage was FCFS, HA would spend this entire week doing nothing but Skyfire raiding, and would have an epic cleric within a week of their first cleric becoming Rage ready.  You know this is almost a certainty.  I don't know if you have rage ready clerics in guild.  If so, ask yourself how long have they been ready?  How long would they still have to wait for their epic under the current list?  <br><br>Your biggest competition over a FCFS Ragefire, is going to be from other guilds in YOUR league.  Other guilds that need that first or second clicky stick cleric.<br><br>There is no way in hell that FCFS leaves more Rage's up than reservations.  FCFS rewards people for TWO reasons.  One is ability (which frightens all younger guilds).  Second, is desire.  The guilds most desparate for the Epic, will get their epic soonest.  The only time you will be KSed by an "uber" guild, is when their desire for a stick begins to approach yours, and they can trump you in ability.<br><br>And even should that happen once or twice.  It's still better than submitting to "claim" the 22nd spawn from the date you are ready.  Basically you are conceding 21 spawns to be "KSed" from you by agreement.  Not all clerics (well, more appropriately: GUILDS) on this list have the same level of pure need.  There is currently no way for a guild or cleric to do anything proactive, to address this.<br><br>I can see the value of a reservation system, when there are a large number of epic ready guilds all desparate for their first or second rez stick.  There aren't that many dragon capable guilds that have that same desparation anymore.  The pure NEED for a list has long since passed now that the server population has matured.  <br><br>The time where a Rage rotation is needed to avoid bad blood amongst guilds has long passed.  In fact, the inflexible rotation now only serves to promote bad blood between those that really need their epics, and many of the others that do not.<br><br><br> <p>Emmalythe 29th lvl teabagger armswoman (retired)<br>Iron Fist guild - Palomides<br><br>Attyla the Unguilded<br>43rd Troll Shadowknight<br>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#B8C0C7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/usojo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sojo1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Torvonnite</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#122950>(2/1/02 11:16:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2445.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire, FCFS or Rotation?</span><hr size=1> FcFs = ) <p>-Soj <br> Court of Pain</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C5C5BA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uxeroband.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xeroband</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Torvonnite</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#122950>(2/1/02 11:22:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2445.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://staff.washington.edu/toughguy/bruce.gif width=78 height=59></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire, FCFS or Rotation?</span><hr size=1> If I cared anymore I'd say fcfs. <p><center><image src="http://staff.washington.edu/toughguy/xerosig1.jpg"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3795">Groovy</a><br><i>"Even though a man may have more hairs on his head than there are stars in the sky, that doesn't mean that he can 