le on every single night of the week to drop Ragefire - by 2pm est.<br><br>However to me it's always seemed pretty pathetic to take advantage of something whilst it suits you then ignore/abuse it when it is no longer in your best interests.<br><br>As long as the Ragefire rotation remains intact as it was pre-patch then NoF will continue to adhere to it. However if Eternal Rage is going FCFS we will reconsider and we will also reconsider our following the VS rotation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#B8C0C7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulathlarien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lathlarien</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Torvonnite</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#122950>(2/2/02 1:51:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2445.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire, FCFS or Rotation?</span><hr size=1> Atylla, you know he was buffed, right ? A smaller guild thats &quot;xping&quot; in Skyfire and which is not filled with upper fifties and 60ies will not have an easy task with the now lvl60 Ragefire. He will fear lower levels much easier than before. Thus, that guild would need to not only organise their own guild they would also need to recruit some outside help to do the job. How long do you think that a higher level guild would wait for that after its known that Ragefire spawned ? How many wipes and despawns will we see due to hastely put together Ragefire attempts ? This is a WASTE of spawns, and youre dull if you dont see it. Use the list and use the 4 hour window time slot and then move on with next on list. This is not the 2 group encounter is was (still would be for high end guilds thou) and making him despawn is lame.<br><br>Lath